references:
Our experimental evaluation showcases the efficacy of the DDPG-CIDS framework across several datasets, including MovieLens-100k, MovieLens-1M, Douban-Book, and BookCrossing. We benchmarked against a range of state-of-the-art algorithms and highlighted the best and second-best results with bold and asterisks, respectively, as detailed in Table 1.
Particularly on MovieLens-100k, DDPG-CIDS surpassed all baselines, reinforcing the benefits of integrating CIDS into the recommendation mechanism. Its top scores in Recall, Precision, and Accuracy highlight the method’s effectiveness. On the larger MovieLens-1M, DDPG-CIDS maintained top-tier results, suggesting scalability.
DDPG-CIDS’s superior performance on the Douban-Book and BookCrossing datasets confirmed its adaptability to various content types and user interactions.
